text.section:
The Administration may:
Prepare plans for the program;
Adopt necessary rules and regulations to carry out these plans;
In accordance with these plans, receive and spend any available funds;
Coordinate and supervise the provision of program services that the Administration does not provide directly; and
Cooperate with the federal government and with all other public or private agencies in:
Developing, extending, and improving the services; and
Carrying out the plans.
